The paper deals with the design of data markets and the allocation of data to competing firms, which involves game-theoretic considerations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models and predictions, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with the allocation and pricing of multiple data sets, which involves optimization and algorithmic considerations, suggesting that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the design of optimal mechanisms for auctions with externalities, which suggests that it could also belong to the Electronic Commerce (cs.EC) sub-category.
